# Step 3: Database Management Dashboard UI

**Phase:** 10 -- Database Management
**Step:** 3 of 4
**Type:** Frontend implementation
**Depends on:** Step 2 (API routes must be implemented for the UI to fetch and mutate data)
**Blocks:** None (Step 4 is complementary, not sequential)

---

## Objective

Replace the placeholder database page with a full-featured UI that handles three states: loading, no database (create prompt), and database exists (info panel with stats, connection string, and delete option). The page uses SWR for data fetching and provides a responsive, polished experience consistent with the rest of the dashboard.

---

## Current State

The file `apps/dashboard/src/app/projects/[id]/database/page.tsx` exists as a placeholder:

```tsx
import { Placeholder } from "@/components/ui/placeholder";

export default function DatabasePage() {
  return <Placeholder title="Database Management" />;
}
```

This page is part of the project detail view, accessible via the "Database" tab at `/projects/:id/database`.

---

## Page States

### State 1: Loading
Display a skeleton UI while `GET /api/projects/:id/database` is in flight. Show skeleton shapes for the database info panel (name, connection string, stats area) to prevent layout shift.

### State 2: No Database (GET returns `null`)
Display an empty state with:
- Heading: "No Database"
- Description: "Create a PostgreSQL database for this project. A connection string will be automatically configured as the DATABASE_URL environment variable."
- "Create Database" primary button
- Info note: "The database will be created on the shared RDS instance with a dedicated user and random password."

### State 3: Database Exists
Display the `DatabasePanel` component with:
- Database name and user (read-only display)
- Connection string with show/hide password toggle (Step 4 component)
- Stats: database size (formatted), active connections
- Creation date
- Info badge: "DATABASE_URL is set for production and preview"
- "Delete Database" danger button (at bottom, in a "Danger Zone" section)

---

## Components to Create

### 1. `apps/dashboard/src/components/database/database-panel.tsx`

Main panel that displays all database info. Receives the database info object as props.

```typescript
interface DatabaseInfo {
  dbName: string;
  dbUser: string;
  sizeBytes: number;
  activeConnections: number;
  connectionString: string;
  createdAt: string;
}

interface DatabasePanelProps {
  database: DatabaseInfo;
  onDelete: () => void;
}
```

**Layout:**
```
+-----------------------------------------------+
| Database: app_myproject                        |
| User: app_myproject_user                       |
+-----------------------------------------------+
| Connection String                              |
| [postgresql://...****...?sslmode=require]  [Copy] |
|                                    [Show/Hide] |
+-----------------------------------------------+
| Stats                                          |
| Size: 8.2 MB  |  Connections: 2               |
| Created: March 1, 2026                         |
+-----------------------------------------------+
| [i] DATABASE_URL is set for production and     |
|     preview environments                       |
+-----------------------------------------------+
|                                                |
| Danger Zone                                    |
| [Delete Database]                              |
+-----------------------------------------------+
```

### 2. `apps/dashboard/src/components/database/connection-string.tsx`

Displays the connection string with:
- Monospace font
- Password masked by default (replaced with `********`)
- Eye icon button to toggle password visibility
- Copy button that copies the FULL connection string (with real password)
- Visual feedback on copy (checkmark icon + "Copied!" text for 2 seconds)

See Step 4 spec for full details on this component.

### 3. `apps/dashboard/src/components/database/create-database-dialog.tsx`

Confirmation dialog for creating a database.

**Content:**
- Title: "Create Database"
- Body: "This will create a PostgreSQL database named `app_{slug}` on the shared RDS instance. A `DATABASE_URL` environment variable will be automatically set for both production and preview environments."
- Cancel button
- "Create Database" primary button with loading state

**Behavior:**
- On confirm: `POST /api/projects/:id/database`
- Show loading spinner on the confirm button
- On success: close dialog, trigger SWR revalidation
- On error: display error message in the dialog (keep it open)

### 4. `apps/dashboard/src/components/database/delete-database-dialog.tsx`

Double-confirmation dialog for deleting a database.

**Content:**
- Title: "Delete Database"
- Warning: "This action is irreversible. The database `{dbName}` and all its data will be permanently deleted. The DATABASE_URL environment variable will be removed."
- Input field: "Type the database name to confirm" with placeholder `{dbName}`
- Cancel button
- "Delete Database" danger button (disabled until input matches `dbName`)

**Behavior:**
- Delete button enabled only when input exactly matches `dbName`
- On confirm: `DELETE /api/projects/:id/database` with body `{ confirmName: inputValue }`
- Show loading spinner on the confirm button
- On success: close dialog, trigger SWR revalidation
- On error: display error message in the dialog

---

## Page Implementation

### Data Fetching

Use SWR for the database info:

```typescript
import useSWR from "swr";

const { data, error, isLoading, mutate } = useSWR(
  `/api/projects/${projectId}/database`,
  fetcher,
);
```

### Size Formatting

Format `sizeBytes` into a human-readable string:
- `< 1024` -> `"X bytes"`
- `< 1024 * 1024` -> `"X.X KB"`
- `< 1024 * 1024 * 1024` -> `"X.X MB"`
- Otherwise -> `"X.X GB"`

### Date Formatting

Format `createdAt` as a readable date: "March 1, 2026" using `Intl.DateTimeFormat` or a date library.

---

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS classes consistent with the existing dashboard design
- Cards use rounded borders with subtle shadow
- Danger zone uses red/destructive color scheme
- Connection string area uses monospace font (`font-mono`)
- Dialogs use the existing dialog/modal component from the dashboard's component library
- Responsive: single-column on mobile, two-column stats on desktop

---

## Error Handling

- API fetch error: display an error alert with retry button
- Create error: display error in dialog, keep dialog open for retry
- Delete error: display error in dialog, keep dialog open for retry
- Network error: display "Unable to connect. Check your network connection."

---

